results.name: a(n) = (A117213(n))/(n-th squarefree positive integer).
comment: Product of all primes up to greatest prime factor of n-th squarefree number that do not divide the n-th squarefree number. - _Franklin T. Adams-Watters_, Oct 09 2006
link: Reinhard Zumkeller, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1000
example: 10 is the 7th squarefree integer. And 2*3*5 = 30 is the smallest primorial number divisible by 10 = 2*5. So a(7) = 30/10 = 3.
mathematica: Product[Prime@ i, {i, PrimePi@ FactorInteger[#][[-1, 1]]}]/# & /@ Select[Range@ 52, SquareFreeQ] (* _Michael De Vlieger_, Sep 30 2017 *)
